&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influencer Marketing ist unser wichtigster Kanal. Behandeln wir ihn auch so.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bei ESN macht Influencer Marketing fast 50 % unseres D2C-Umsatzes aus. Das ist kein Awareness-Kanal unter vielen, sondern eine&amp;nbsp;conversion-fokussierte Sales Engine. Das, was unsere D2C-Zahlen wirklich bewegt.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jetzt skalieren wir: mehr Märkte, mehr Kategorien, mehr Komplexität. Und wir brauchen jemanden, der dafür sorgt, dass unser Influencer Marketing Team noch stärker werden kann.&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deine Mission bei uns&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unsere Community und unsere Creator haben ESN zu dem gemacht, was es heute ist. Auf echten Beziehungen, auf Vertrauen, auf Content, der wirklich bewegt. Was wir jetzt hinzufügen: Insightsund Analysen, die unsere Creator voranbringen und uns helfen, noch proaktiver zu steuern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du übersetzt D2C-Strategie in konkrete Creator-Ziele, nach Markt und Kategorie. So konkret, dass das Influencer Marketing Team direkt damit arbeiten kann.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du tauchst tief in die Performance ein: welche Creator wachsen, welche Märkte performen unter Potenzial, welche Kategorien zu wenig bespielt werden. Du weißt es, und du weißt, was daraus folgt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du hältst den strategischen Rhythmus am Laufen: Reviews mit dem Influencer Marketing Team, Sessions mit Top-Creatorn, Abstimmungen mit internationalen Märkten. Aus jedemdieser Momente werden Entscheidungen, keine Statusupdates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du siehst Risiken früh: Abhängigkeit von einzelnen Creatorn, Kategorie-Mix, der nicht stimmt, Märkte, die driften. Du flagst, du handelst.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du baust unsere Creator-Plattform mit auf: Tools, Frameworks, Reportings, die unser Team und unsere Creator zu State of the Art bringen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Deine Erfahrung &amp;amp; Skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du hast 4–6 Jahre Berufserfahrung in Marketing, Strategy, Consulting oder D2C, idealerweise mit Bezug zu Konsumgütern, E-Commerce oder Creator-Marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du denkst analytisch und kommerziell. Excel ist dein Werkzeug. Du baust Analysen, nicht nur Reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du übersetzt komplexe Daten in einfache Empfehlungen und stehst hinter ihnen, auch im Gespräch mit Senior Stakeholdern.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social-Media-savvy und am Puls der Zeit. Du verbringst viel Zeit auf Instagram und TikTok, du lebst Creator-Logiken täglich.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du arbeitest gerne im Maschinenraum, baust Strukturen, Cadences und Frameworks. Kein reiner Stratege, sondern jemand, der Dinge zum Laufen bringt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Du bist beziehungsstark. Du kannst challengen, ohne anzuecken. Eine zentrale Stimme zum Influencer Marketing-Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sprichst fließend Deutsch und Englisch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Warum wir?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;258&quot; data-end=&quot;599&quot;&gt;Bei The Quality Group arbeiten über 1.200 Menschen mit einer gemeinsamen Mission: Ernährung neu zu denken - gesünder, smarter und mit echtem Mehrwert für die Community.&lt;br data-start=&quot;434&quot; data-end=&quot;437&quot;&gt;Wir glauben an Teamgeist, Eigenverantwortung und den Mut, Grenzen zu verschieben. Dabei zählt jeder Beitrag, unabhängig vom Standort oder Bereich.&lt;br&gt;Je nachdem, wo du bei uns einsteigst, erwarten dich unterschiedliche Benefits, unter anderem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attraktive Mitarbeiterrabatte auf Produkte von ESN &amp;amp; More&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;Start: Immediately | Level: Mid | Location: Hamburg, hybrid | Working Hours: Full Time (40h/Week)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Data Analyst (gn)&lt;/strong&gt;, you will join our &lt;strong&gt;Business Insights Team&lt;/strong&gt; within the &lt;strong&gt;Digital Department&lt;/strong&gt; and play a key role in enabling data-driven decision-making across The Quality Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Our mission is simple: empower the business through reliable data, meaningful insights, and scalable analytics. In this role, you&#39;ll work across the entire analytics lifecycle—from understanding business challenges and transforming raw data into business-ready datasets to building dashboards, delivering actionable insights, and driving data-informed decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe the best analysts combine technical excellence with a strong business mindset. That&#39;s why you&#39;ll collaborate closely with stakeholders, take ownership across the full analytics process, and continuously expand your expertise. Whether your passion lies in data modeling, dashboard development, stakeholder consulting, data quality, or analytics best practices, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to shape both your own development and the future of Business Insights at TQG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You partner with stakeholders across the business to understand challenges and translate them into scalable analytical solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You build and maintain reliable, scalable datasets and reporting tables using SQL and modern transformation tools such as dbt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You design, develop, and optimize dashboards that enable data-driven decision-making across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You perform analyses to identify trends, opportunities, and actionable business insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You define, implement, and continuously improve KPIs, metrics, and reporting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You ensure high data quality through testing, validation, and structured analytical workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You contribute to the continuous improvement of our analytics ecosystem by enhancing documentation, standards, reusable assets, and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take ownership of specific focus areas within the team and actively strengthen our overall analytics capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Your experience &amp;amp; skills&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 2 years of experience in Data Analytics, Business Intelligence, Analytics Engineering, or a comparable role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong SQL skills and enjoy working with data on a daily basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have hands-on experience with modern data transformation tools such as dbt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience building dashboards using BI tools such as Tableau, Looker, or Power BI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You understand data warehouse concepts and enjoy translating business questions into scalable analytical solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate confidently with both technical and non-technical stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You work independently, take ownership, and approach challenges with a structured and solution-oriented mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are fluent in English; German language skills are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are based in or willing to relocate to the Hamburg area and enjoy collaborating with your team on-site on a regular basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why choose u

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;Start: Immediately | Level: Senior | Location: Hamburg, hybrid | Working hours: Fulltime (40h/week)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As Data Architect (gn) – Master Data Management, you bear the overall technical and structural responsibility for the architecture of our master data management. In this role, you define the global master data model, design validation rules and workflows, and ensure that data structures are perfectly harmonized across all systems. You will act as the central technical authority at the crucial interface between business requirements and IT implementation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The role can be done fully remote with occasional visits in the HQ in Hamburg (about 1x month in the first year, afterwards less).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot;&gt;You hold overall ownership of the master data model and attribute logic across all relevant domains. You define field attributes, mandatory fields, and validation rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot;&gt;You establish the leading system (System of Record / SOR) for each master data object, document the data flows within the system landscape, and define synchronization logics, replication rules, and error handling in close coordination with the integration teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot;&gt;You assume technical responsibility for all MDM-relevant interfaces between SAP, PIM (Akeneo), CRM, WMS (Lea), PLM (Centric), and other systems. In doing so, you reduce complexity, avoid technical workarounds, and support data migrations from extraction to validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,3,0&quot;&gt;You design and document end-to-end master data processes. You define the workflows for data creation, enrichment, approval, and distribution, and systematically close process gaps at system handover points across all domains (Product, Vendor, Customer, Finance, Logistics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,4,0&quot;&gt;You implement data quality rules within the systems, monitor technical MDM key performance indicators (KPIs), and drive continuous improvement processes from a technical perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;5,5,0&quot;&gt;You ensure stable interfaces to downstream systems and are responsible for seamless, top-tier documentation of data models and integration architectures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Your experience &amp;amp; skills&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,0,0&quot;&gt;You bring at least 6 years of solid professional experience in data architecture, MDM, or SAP master data management, and have a proven track record of modeling master data structures in large-scale transformation projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;Ideally, you possess a solid understanding of the FMCG, food, dietary supplements, or retail industries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;You have deep knowledge of SAP master data (Material, Business Partner, Pricing, BOM, etc.) and are fully proficient with PIM and PLM systems as well as modern system integrations (API, ETL, etc.). A clear understanding of CRM, WMS, and e-commerce landscapes rounds off your profile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,3,0&quot;&gt;You are characterized by a highly analytical and structured mindset, with the ability to translate complex technical topics clearly for business stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;7,4,0&quot;&gt;An autonomous, quality-driven working style is second nature to you. You stand out as a team player and speak fluent German and English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why choose us?&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;Start: Immediately | Level: Director | Location: Hamburg, hybrid, Berlin, remote | Type: Full time (40h/week)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As &lt;strong&gt;Director (gn) Global Brand&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be the architect of how ESN shows up to the world. This is not a blank-sheet brief — ESN has a strong heritage, a fiercely loyal community, and real brand equity built over years.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;Your job is to take that foundation and elevate it: sharpening the strategy, building a visual identity and design system that sets a new standard for the category, and raising the creative bar across every touchpoint so that ESN&#39;s brand power matches its commercial ambition. But strategy and systems are only half the job. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun MacChromeBold SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW104639616 BCX0&quot;&gt;The bigger gap — and the bigger opportunity — is brand moments. ESN has the athletes, the community, and the products to create moments that define the brand culturally: flagship experiences that the sports world talks about, product launches that feel like cultural events, campaign concepts that earn attention rather than buy it. This role owns that creative vision end to end. You will work directly with the GM Brand and the leads of D2C, Portfolio &amp;amp; Commercial, and International to bring these moments to life at scale. We are looking for someone who is both deeply strategic and genuinely creative — someone with the experience to build a brand system and the vision and creative courage to produce ideas that make people stop and feel something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,0,0&quot;&gt;You drive the master brand strategy (positioning, architecture, tone of voice, and visual identity) — optimized for the German core market and scalable for international expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,1,0&quot;&gt;You are responsible for bold brand experiences and athlete-led events that act as cultural statements to capture global attention and deepen long-term community loyalty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,2,0&quot;&gt;You hold end-to-end responsibility (from concept to execution standards) for the creative presentation during major commercial moments, product launches, and relevant community experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,3,0&quot;&gt;You establish a strategic architecture and set of principles that empower international teams to adapt the brand with local relevance while maintaining global consistency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,4,0&quot;&gt;You implement a distinctive visual design language across packaging, digital, retail, and content through practical guidelines and templates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,5,0&quot;&gt;You serve as the central brand authority for all internal stakeholders (D2C, Commercial, International) and lead as well as brief global creative and brand agencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Your experience &amp;amp; skills&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,0,0&quot;&gt;You bring 12+ years of leadership experience in brand management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-path-to-node=&quot;1,0,0&quot;&gt;You have extensive senior-level experience at a culture and lifestyle brand (e.g., Nike, Adidas, Red Bull, Gymshark level) and ideally additional agency e

